This paper deals with a graph optimization problem related to credit risk management, which involves assigning securities to accounts in a balanced way. This problem can be modeled as a maximum flow problem with capacity constraints, and the objective is to minimize a quadratic function of the unsecured parts of the accounts. This type of problem is commonly studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), computational complexity (cs.CC), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
